1
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:19,465
Taxi!

2
00:00:23,665 --> 00:00:25,585
- Madh island?
- Madh island. Okay, sir.

3
00:00:51,145 --> 00:00:53,625
<i>- Sir?</i>
- Wasim! All okay?

4
00:00:53,705 --> 00:00:54,785
All okay, sir.

5
00:00:54,865 --> 00:00:56,065
Hand over the phone to madam.

6
00:00:56,585 --> 00:00:59,145
I'm at my kid's school, sir.
For a parent-teacher meeting.

7
00:01:00,465 --> 00:01:02,345
Who the hell was going to inform me?

8
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:06,145
Sorry, sir. I had informed madam.

9
00:01:08,865 --> 00:01:09,785
Hit the gas.

10
00:01:46,985 --> 00:01:47,865
Priya!

11
00:02:09,625 --> 00:02:10,505
Arjun?

12
00:02:11,225 --> 00:02:12,425
Why did you send Waseem away?

13
00:02:12,985 --> 00:02:14,705
- Arjun, his kid--
- You should've called me.

14
00:02:15,345 --> 00:02:17,465
He had a parent-teacher meeting
at his kid's school.

15
00:02:17,545 --> 00:02:19,145
But what's the matter? Tell me.

16
00:02:29,505 --> 00:02:31,785
I spared Priya today, Arjun.

17
00:02:35,025 --> 00:02:35,865
Mend your ways.

18
00:02:37,105 --> 00:02:39,345
Because if you don't listen to me,

19
00:02:40,265 --> 00:02:41,785
then I will hunt her down.

20
00:02:43,105 --> 00:02:45,585
She'll die a death much worse than Gujjar.

21
00:02:47,385 --> 00:02:48,945
You can change the safe house,

22
00:02:49,625 --> 00:02:51,105
but I'll track her down.

23
00:02:51,745 --> 00:02:54,185
You can change again, I'll find her again.

24
00:02:55,185 --> 00:02:59,545
All the safe houses in the world won't be
enough for you to hide her, Arjun Meena.

25
00:03:01,425 --> 00:03:04,785
So don't forget
how valuable today's gift was.

26
00:03:09,745 --> 00:03:11,225
What happened? Who was it?

27
00:03:13,385 --> 00:03:14,305
Pack your stuff.

28
00:03:15,185 --> 00:03:16,825
I will have to move you somewhere else.

29
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:19,225
Choudhary knows about this safe house.
Come on.

30
00:03:19,305 --> 00:03:20,825
Wait a second, wait a second!

31
00:03:21,905 --> 00:03:23,225
Priya, try and understand.

32
00:03:25,105 --> 00:03:26,465
- Priya, please.
- Arjun!

33
00:03:29,345 --> 00:03:30,705
I can't take this anymore.

34
00:03:31,745 --> 00:03:32,585
Priya!

35
00:05:00,225 --> 00:05:01,665
Send Arjun Meena in here.

36
00:05:17,545 --> 00:05:20,865
<i>The number you are trying</i>
<i>to call is currently not reachable.</i>

37
00:05:25,425 --> 00:05:26,265
Come in.

38
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:31,545
How are you?

39
00:05:34,385 --> 00:05:36,025
I am good, sir.

40
00:05:37,785 --> 00:05:39,945
The situation
has gotten out of hand, Arjun.

41
00:05:41,065 --> 00:05:44,985
Mukim's custodial death,
Ramesh bhai being killed by this Dhuria,

42
00:05:45,065 --> 00:05:46,865
and now Gujjar's murder.

43
00:05:49,985 --> 00:05:52,265
I'm transferring your team
to the back office.

44
00:05:54,025 --> 00:05:57,585
Lie low. Back track. And plan a strategy.

45
00:05:59,305 --> 00:06:01,025
We have to get this bastard.

46
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:04,785
Yes, sir.

47
00:06:09,585 --> 00:06:10,425
Arjun!

48
00:06:11,345 --> 00:06:12,185
Sir.

49
00:06:12,265 --> 00:06:15,545
There were three watches
listed as seized by Gujjar.

50
00:06:16,385 --> 00:06:18,025
His informer's name is missing.

51
00:06:19,145 --> 00:06:20,265
Do you know who it is?

52
00:06:20,345 --> 00:06:23,505
<i>I saw the report. There</i>
<i>were three luxury watches in your name.</i>

53
00:06:23,585 --> 00:06:26,025
You want to keep
your informer a secret, bastard?

54
00:06:27,265 --> 00:06:28,505
No. No idea, sir.

55
00:06:29,705 --> 00:06:32,505
Gujjar's informer is still there
in Choudhary Syndicate?

56
00:06:33,665 --> 00:06:35,105
But nobody knows who it is.

57
00:06:39,025 --> 00:06:40,665
They are worth 50 crores.

58
00:06:41,385 --> 00:06:43,625
The informer
would've gotten a hefty reward.

59
00:06:46,385 --> 00:06:47,985
- Okay.
- Sir.

60
00:07:28,225 --> 00:07:29,385
Shrikant Saxena.

61
00:07:37,225 --> 00:07:40,425
When Ravinder and I were close,

62
00:07:42,065 --> 00:07:44,465
he used to share everything with me.

63
00:07:45,505 --> 00:07:47,505
One day, I asked him…

64
00:07:47,585 --> 00:07:50,345
Who do you trust the most in your batch?

65
00:07:50,425 --> 00:07:53,465
Arjun. You've met him, right?

66
00:07:53,545 --> 00:07:54,425
Yes.

67
00:07:58,745 --> 00:07:59,865
Meenu?

68
00:07:59,945 --> 00:08:02,105
In case something happens to me, remember…

69
00:08:02,705 --> 00:08:03,945
What nonsense?

70
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:05,025
Hey, listen to me.

71
00:08:07,225 --> 00:08:10,745
In case something happens to me,
you must share this name with Arjun.

72
00:08:11,425 --> 00:08:13,705
Superintendent Shrikant Saxena.

73
00:08:14,265 --> 00:08:15,705
He will know what to do.

74
00:08:17,825 --> 00:08:18,745
Please?

75
00:08:18,825 --> 00:08:20,345
Nothing's gonna happen to you.

76
00:08:21,265 --> 00:08:24,465
Okay, my love. Nothing will happen.
But just in case…

77
00:08:28,145 --> 00:08:30,865
Okay. Tell me what's the name I told you?

78
00:08:31,465 --> 00:08:33,985
Superintendent Shrikant Saxena.

79
00:08:51,545 --> 00:08:52,905
- Awasthi.
<i>- Sir?</i>

80
00:08:52,985 --> 00:08:56,785
I need Superintendent Shrikant Saxena's
address. Right away.

81
00:09:04,865 --> 00:09:07,385
Sharma <i>ji,</i> Arjun needs to be dealt with.

82
00:09:07,945 --> 00:09:09,345
He's made life hell for us.

83
00:09:15,385 --> 00:09:16,385
Sharma <i>ji.</i>

84
00:09:18,105 --> 00:09:19,625
Oh, Arbab sahib!

85
00:09:21,505 --> 00:09:24,105
- How are you?
- I'm fine.

86
00:09:26,825 --> 00:09:28,425
Omar sahib was remembering you.

87
00:09:29,145 --> 00:09:31,105
But we are headed to the hotel.

88
00:09:31,745 --> 00:09:34,225
You can go later. Come on.

89
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:37,225
- Sharma <i>ji,</i> what is this?
- We'll have to go.

90
00:11:03,585 --> 00:11:07,625
Omar sahib gave you
500 kilos of gold on my assurance.

91
00:11:08,345 --> 00:11:11,105
You had promised three days.
It's been eight days.

92
00:11:17,105 --> 00:11:20,665
Omar sahib wants to now
when will you pay him back?

93
00:11:24,545 --> 00:11:25,825
Look, Omar sahib…

94
00:11:30,705 --> 00:11:33,705
Omar sahib, what happened
was that the consignment…

95
00:11:37,985 --> 00:11:38,865
Thank you.

96
00:11:41,465 --> 00:11:42,465
Excuse me.

97
00:11:54,665 --> 00:11:57,465
- Hello?
<i>- I have bad news for you, Choudhary sahib.</i>

98
00:11:58,225 --> 00:11:59,985
<i>I am going through Priya's file.</i>

99
00:12:00,065 --> 00:12:03,665
<i>She only gave tips about gold and drugs,</i>
<i>as she knew about those.</i>

100
00:12:05,345 --> 00:12:07,585
<i>She wasn't even aware of the watches.</i>

101
00:12:09,305 --> 00:12:11,425
<i>There's somebody else in your Syndicate,</i>

102
00:12:11,505 --> 00:12:14,425
<i>who is informing the Customs,</i>
<i>Choudhary sahib.</i>

103
00:12:16,825 --> 00:12:20,625
<i>Find him or we will keep on taking hits.</i>

104
00:12:22,625 --> 00:12:23,825
I know who it is.

105
00:12:29,025 --> 00:12:30,225
Tell me something.

106
00:12:32,225 --> 00:12:36,025
I want to send two tons of goods
in two days. Will you be able to manage?

107
00:12:37,025 --> 00:12:39,745
I will have to, as we are partners now.

108
00:12:41,065 --> 00:12:44,465
It will be done. Don't you worry at all.

109
00:12:45,465 --> 00:12:46,385
Okay.

110
00:13:07,585 --> 00:13:09,985
My system takes care
of a lot of people and families.

111
00:13:10,505 --> 00:13:14,025
And even I don't know
to what extent I can go to protect them.

112
00:13:24,945 --> 00:13:26,145
I'll have to learn.

113
00:13:27,945 --> 00:13:30,265
I'll have to learn this style,
Choudhary sahib.

114
00:13:31,265 --> 00:13:36,265
And in this process of learning, why don't
I help expand and strengthen your system?

115
00:13:39,305 --> 00:13:40,945
Want to talk business, Choudhary sahib?

116
00:13:47,945 --> 00:13:50,185
Good, you showed me your true colors.

117
00:13:50,265 --> 00:13:53,105
I had almost started trusting humanity.

118
00:13:55,745 --> 00:13:56,985
Here's my offer.

119
00:13:59,745 --> 00:14:01,425
Twenty percent of all profits.

120
00:14:02,545 --> 00:14:03,865
After expenses.

121
00:14:04,985 --> 00:14:07,865
As part of expenses,
sometimes your goods might be seized.

122
00:14:08,585 --> 00:14:09,865
Don't mind that.

123
00:14:11,505 --> 00:14:13,985
What will I get in return for this 20%?

124
00:14:14,065 --> 00:14:16,225
You will get Mumbai International Airport,

125
00:14:17,025 --> 00:14:18,145
including Customs.

126
00:14:21,345 --> 00:14:22,705
Why didn't you say this earlier?

127
00:14:24,025 --> 00:14:25,665
You seized so much of our stuff.

128
00:14:26,785 --> 00:14:28,025
You could've said it upfront.

129
00:14:28,545 --> 00:14:29,945
Valuation, Choudhary sahib.

130
00:14:31,825 --> 00:14:33,825
I had to wait for the correct valuation.

131
00:14:35,985 --> 00:14:39,265
Now that you know
how much pain I can cause you,

132
00:14:41,705 --> 00:14:43,825
it'll be easier for you to evaluate

133
00:14:44,385 --> 00:14:46,305
the true value of my worth.

134
00:14:50,985 --> 00:14:53,905
What about this army of good guys
that you've brought to the airport?

135
00:14:54,545 --> 00:14:57,425
I brought them in. I'll take them out too.

136
00:14:58,905 --> 00:14:59,745
Hmm.

137
00:15:02,265 --> 00:15:04,865
So you wish to ride the lion?

138
00:15:04,945 --> 00:15:07,385
We only live once, Choudhary sahib.

139
00:15:08,545 --> 00:15:11,065
What's the fun
if one didn't even ride the lion?

140
00:15:16,025 --> 00:15:18,585
- Deal.
- Thanks.

141
00:15:19,905 --> 00:15:23,065
Now that we are partners,
here's my first piece of information.

142
00:15:24,385 --> 00:15:27,985
One of my teams is going to raid
Ramesh bhai's house at 10:30 a.m. sharp.

143
00:15:29,545 --> 00:15:32,385
If Ramesh bhai survives, it's good for us.

144
00:15:33,505 --> 00:15:34,985
And if he dies,

145
00:15:35,545 --> 00:15:38,305
that too at the hands
of one of my Customs' team member,

146
00:15:38,385 --> 00:15:40,145
that'll be more profitable for us.

147
00:15:42,425 --> 00:15:45,385
We have a new recruit, Kulveer Dhuria.

148
00:15:46,185 --> 00:15:48,425
He is greedy. He's broke.

149
00:15:49,905 --> 00:15:51,305
Offer him a crore.

150
00:16:24,865 --> 00:16:27,425
<i>- Hello.</i>
- Why did you do that to me?

151
00:16:48,145 --> 00:16:51,585
Omar sahib,
I'll pay you back in full by next week.

152
00:16:53,225 --> 00:16:55,585
{\an8}But for that, you'll have
to give me two more tons.

153
00:16:59,905 --> 00:17:02,905
What do you think?
Should we trust him again?

154
00:17:04,465 --> 00:17:06,585
He is here, sir, talk to him.

155
00:17:07,745 --> 00:17:08,785
Look, Omar sahib.

156
00:17:09,905 --> 00:17:13,145
You know one has to spend money
to earn money.

157
00:17:13,825 --> 00:17:15,625
{\an8}As soon as
this consignment lands in India,

158
00:17:16,505 --> 00:17:20,105
{\an8}all your debt,
old and new will be paid off.

159
00:17:24,265 --> 00:17:25,545
How will you send it?

160
00:17:26,505 --> 00:17:29,865
And what's the guarantee
that it won't be seized this time?

161
00:17:31,865 --> 00:17:33,945
{\an8}Trust me, Omar sahib.

162
00:17:35,545 --> 00:17:38,105
{\an8}Nobody will dare touch this batch.

163
00:18:32,705 --> 00:18:34,025
Sorry, Choudhary sahib.

164
00:18:34,105 --> 00:18:38,705
Arbab hadn't mentioned that he'd take you
straight to Omar sahib from the airport.

165
00:18:38,785 --> 00:18:40,265
It wasn't right on his part.

166
00:18:42,385 --> 00:18:44,065
He's taken a big hit.

167
00:18:44,985 --> 00:18:47,025
Had I been in his shoes,
I'd have done even worse.

168
00:18:48,305 --> 00:18:50,625
Rahul, you got Priya
into the Syndicate, right?

169
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:52,625
Yes, Choudhary sahib.

170
00:18:53,545 --> 00:18:54,625
I'm sorry for that.

171
00:18:54,705 --> 00:18:55,745
No, no. Don't be.

172
00:18:56,905 --> 00:18:58,665
You'll make up for it. Trust me.

173
00:18:59,785 --> 00:19:00,865
Suresh.

174
00:19:01,705 --> 00:19:04,025
There is only one way
out of this mire for us.

175
00:19:05,225 --> 00:19:06,145
Sharma <i>ji?</i>

176
00:19:07,305 --> 00:19:09,065
We have to send two tons of gold to India.

177
00:19:09,745 --> 00:19:12,065
- In the next 48 hours.
- Two tons?

178
00:19:14,105 --> 00:19:15,185
In one shipment?

179
00:19:16,105 --> 00:19:19,185
Forty Indian tourists
have died in an accident.

180
00:19:20,305 --> 00:19:23,945
Suresh, you are the only one
who can do this.

181
00:19:24,865 --> 00:19:27,785
Doctors are on standby in Al Rasheed.
And if we wish--

182
00:19:27,865 --> 00:19:30,185
No. Body concealment?

183
00:19:31,105 --> 00:19:32,305
It will be very risky.

184
00:19:34,505 --> 00:19:38,305
Caskets, I mean coffins will be perfect
for such a large consignment.

185
00:20:44,825 --> 00:20:47,785
Superintendent Arjun Meena. Come in.

186
00:20:49,465 --> 00:20:50,465
Take off your shoes.

187
00:20:50,545 --> 00:20:51,385
Sure, sir.

188
00:21:12,945 --> 00:21:17,785
My wife, Suman passed away three months
before I was released from prison.

189
00:21:19,065 --> 00:21:20,265
I'm sorry, sir.

190
00:21:20,345 --> 00:21:21,745
And I'm sorry for Gujjar.

191
00:21:23,065 --> 00:21:26,625
I had told him to stay level-headed.
But no.

192
00:21:28,705 --> 00:21:31,865
Youngsters, these days
hardly listen to the elders.

193
00:21:34,945 --> 00:21:39,065
Twelve years ago, when I was terminated
based on a false accusation of corruption,

194
00:21:39,585 --> 00:21:42,825
I had a source in the Al Dera Syndicate.

195
00:21:44,625 --> 00:21:47,185
And he is still active today.

196
00:21:48,105 --> 00:21:51,505
He sent me intel about the watches.
And I passed it on to Gujjar.

197
00:21:52,305 --> 00:21:56,865
Gujjar had told me that if anything
happened to him, I should tell you this.

198
00:21:58,065 --> 00:22:00,425
{\an8}<i>There were three watches</i>
<i>listed as seized by Gujjar.</i>

199
00:22:00,505 --> 00:22:02,265
The informer's name is missing.

200
00:22:02,345 --> 00:22:03,505
<i>Do you know who it is?</i>

201
00:22:18,985 --> 00:22:19,825
Timing.

202
00:22:38,705 --> 00:22:39,785
Yes, Zubair. Tell me.

203
00:22:40,305 --> 00:22:43,225
Sahib, two tons of Choudhary's gold
will land in Mumbai

204
00:22:43,305 --> 00:22:45,625
day after tomorrow
in coffins carrying corpses.

205
00:22:45,705 --> 00:22:46,945
<i>- Two tons?</i>
- Yes.

206
00:23:00,985 --> 00:23:03,025
Hey, hello! Please stop.

207
00:23:04,585 --> 00:23:06,585
- Who, sir? Me?
- Yes. Please stop.

208
00:23:13,425 --> 00:23:16,305
- What is it, sir?
- Nothing. What is your name?

209
00:23:16,385 --> 00:23:17,665
Suresh Tande.

210
00:23:18,665 --> 00:23:20,985
- Where are you coming from?
- From Al Dera, sir.

211
00:23:21,905 --> 00:23:23,905
I've scanned my baggage and everything.

212
00:23:25,265 --> 00:23:28,505
Amazing.
You are well versed with our procedure.

213
00:23:29,545 --> 00:23:33,105
Come, I need to do some checking.
Please come.

214
00:23:33,185 --> 00:23:35,305
Come on. Please, please.

215
00:23:35,385 --> 00:23:36,425
Please.

216
00:23:38,585 --> 00:23:41,465
You can see, sir. All household stuff.

217
00:23:43,745 --> 00:23:47,345
Look, my kid loves cars, sahib.
He races them.

218
00:23:47,425 --> 00:23:50,145
This chocolate is also for my kid, sahib.

219
00:23:51,345 --> 00:23:53,665
And dates, my family loves these, sahib.

220
00:23:53,745 --> 00:23:55,225
So I brought these for them.

221
00:23:55,305 --> 00:23:57,985
A friend of yours told me
that you're carrying stuff.

222
00:23:59,665 --> 00:24:00,985
He will get rewarded too.

223
00:24:03,225 --> 00:24:07,185
Sahib, there… are more dates.
These are of a better quality.

224
00:24:07,265 --> 00:24:08,785
So I got these too.

225
00:24:08,865 --> 00:24:11,185
Those guys do this because…

226
00:24:12,785 --> 00:24:14,865
while I am busy with your paperwork,

227
00:24:16,425 --> 00:24:19,185
their couriers can pass
through with their stuff.

228
00:24:20,185 --> 00:24:21,385
Do you get it?

229
00:24:35,265 --> 00:24:37,545
How much are you carrying on your body?

230
00:24:39,945 --> 00:24:40,785
Sahib.

231
00:24:43,025 --> 00:24:46,545
Sahib, my wife is really sick, sahib.

232
00:24:48,065 --> 00:24:49,385
It's the last stage, sir.

233
00:24:51,145 --> 00:24:52,585
I am here to see her, sahib.

234
00:24:53,105 --> 00:24:54,105
So sad.

235
00:24:55,065 --> 00:24:57,345
Hey, but how much are you carrying?

236
00:25:01,745 --> 00:25:03,225
I have two kilos, sir.

237
00:25:06,705 --> 00:25:09,185
Look, sir. I will…

238
00:25:10,345 --> 00:25:12,665
surrender all the gold here.

239
00:25:14,185 --> 00:25:15,865
Let me go and see my wife, sahib.

240
00:25:15,945 --> 00:25:19,825
It is more than 50 lakhs.
You will have to be taken to court.

241
00:25:19,905 --> 00:25:22,145
Sahib, please do something.

242
00:25:22,225 --> 00:25:24,625
The courts closed for two days, so you--

243
00:25:24,705 --> 00:25:27,105
- No, sahib. Don't do that.
- You will have to stay here.

244
00:25:27,185 --> 00:25:29,265
- Don't do that, sahib.
- Hey, the courts are off, so…

245
00:25:29,345 --> 00:25:31,625
- You have to stay here for two days.
- Sahib.

246
00:25:31,705 --> 00:25:34,505
I have to see my wife. Please let me go.

247
00:25:34,585 --> 00:25:36,425
I'll keep you in my prayers forever.

248
00:25:37,265 --> 00:25:41,385
Let me go, sahib.
I am willing to do anything, sahib.

249
00:25:41,465 --> 00:25:43,625
Let me go, sahib. Please, sahib.

250
00:25:45,185 --> 00:25:47,865
- Tell me what can you do for me?
- I will do anything, sahib.

251
00:25:49,665 --> 00:25:50,985
I'll do whatever you say.

252
00:25:51,985 --> 00:25:53,225
So tell me…

253
00:25:54,305 --> 00:25:56,265
who gave you the two kilos of gold?

254
00:26:01,225 --> 00:26:05,465
He goes by the name
of Anna Seth, sahib. Anna Seth.

255
00:26:06,905 --> 00:26:09,025
He is a labor contractor, sahib.

256
00:26:10,945 --> 00:26:13,465
He has an office at Dera.

257
00:26:13,545 --> 00:26:14,465
In Al Dera.

258
00:26:15,945 --> 00:26:18,665
Where does this Anna get the gold from?

259
00:26:19,345 --> 00:26:21,065
That I do not know, sahib.

260
00:26:21,145 --> 00:26:23,945
I swear, I do not know. Trust me, sahib.

261
00:26:27,825 --> 00:26:29,305
How long have you known Anna?

262
00:26:29,385 --> 00:26:32,145
He came to Mumbai three years ago, sahib.

263
00:26:32,225 --> 00:26:33,705
He was looking for workers.

264
00:26:33,785 --> 00:26:35,985
And I got hired. I'm a welder, sahib.

265
00:26:36,505 --> 00:26:37,985
When did you start this work?

266
00:26:41,545 --> 00:26:42,905
One year ago, sahib.

267
00:26:44,185 --> 00:26:45,985
I was in dire need of money, sahib.

268
00:26:47,865 --> 00:26:50,585
I was trying to save my wife

269
00:26:50,665 --> 00:26:53,465
at any cost, sahib.

270
00:26:53,545 --> 00:26:56,105
So I was forced to do this, sahib.

271
00:26:57,225 --> 00:27:00,505
Sahib, please let me go, sahib.

272
00:27:01,465 --> 00:27:03,025
Let me go, sahib.

273
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:08,545
Okay, you can go today.

274
00:27:09,505 --> 00:27:10,745
Thank you so much.

275
00:27:10,825 --> 00:27:12,865
But from today onwards,

276
00:27:14,505 --> 00:27:15,905
you will work for me.

277
00:27:17,665 --> 00:27:19,785
I don't get it, sahib.

278
00:27:19,865 --> 00:27:24,265
I mean that from today onwards,
you will work for me

279
00:27:24,345 --> 00:27:27,985
and I'll tell you how to cozy up to Anna.

280
00:27:30,265 --> 00:27:35,105
You will also get rewarded
for the gold you help us seize. Got it?

281
00:27:40,985 --> 00:27:43,265
Okay. I will do that, sahib.

282
00:27:44,305 --> 00:27:45,865
I will do anything.

283
00:27:46,985 --> 00:27:50,265
Okay. Put your clothes on and get going.

284
00:27:52,225 --> 00:27:53,545
Thank you, sahib.

285
00:27:55,225 --> 00:27:57,705
<i>- Two tons?</i>
- Yes, sahib.

286
00:27:57,785 --> 00:28:01,265
Omar sahib is pressurizing him to pay
him back. That's why he is doing this.

287
00:28:01,345 --> 00:28:03,145
I was the one who gave him the idea.

288
00:28:03,225 --> 00:28:04,585
<i>You can forward this intel.</i>

289
00:28:04,665 --> 00:28:08,985
And sahib, if this consignment is seized,
it'll be the end of Choudhary Syndicate.

290
00:28:09,785 --> 00:28:12,585
Okay, sahib, I will leave for Al Dera Mall

291
00:28:13,265 --> 00:28:15,305
after dispatching the consignment.

292
00:28:15,385 --> 00:28:18,185
Now, you have to help me get out of here.

293
00:28:19,505 --> 00:28:20,785
I will try, Zubair.

294
00:28:22,305 --> 00:28:23,545
You are aware that…

295
00:28:25,105 --> 00:28:29,225
Yes, sahib. Your officer,
Ravinder Gujjar got killed.

296
00:28:31,265 --> 00:28:32,505
I get it, sahib.

297
00:28:32,585 --> 00:28:35,425
But don't worry. I will manage somehow.

298
00:28:35,505 --> 00:28:38,185
No, no, no, no! Not you, I will manage.

299
00:28:38,825 --> 00:28:40,985
Okay, sahib, one more thing.

300
00:28:41,065 --> 00:28:44,385
I don't know if this is useful for you,
but Bada Choudhary is here.

301
00:28:46,145 --> 00:28:50,305
And Bada Choudhary will stay here till
his contraband doesn't land in Mumbai.

302
00:28:51,105 --> 00:28:53,585
Keep me posted after every six hours.

303
00:28:54,425 --> 00:28:55,465
Okay, sir.

304
00:29:03,985 --> 00:29:07,385
Forty coffins carrying two tons of gold
are going to land

305
00:29:07,465 --> 00:29:09,305
at Mumbai International Airport

306
00:29:10,345 --> 00:29:11,545
in the next 48 hours.

307
00:29:26,865 --> 00:29:28,425
Put it on the table over there.

308
00:30:37,105 --> 00:30:38,185
<i>Kaka.</i>

309
00:30:49,985 --> 00:30:51,785
He's really betrayed us, Choudhary sahib.

310
00:30:52,705 --> 00:30:55,545
- I will not spare him.
- You can settle that later, Anna.

311
00:30:56,745 --> 00:30:58,345
It's time for our cargo.

312
00:30:59,145 --> 00:31:00,585
Do what I've told you.

313
00:31:02,105 --> 00:31:03,465
Okay, Choudhary sahib.

314
00:31:19,505 --> 00:31:20,545
Yes, Saxena sahib.

315
00:31:20,625 --> 00:31:22,385
My source has been compromised.

316
00:31:22,465 --> 00:31:24,025
<i>His life could be in danger.</i>

317
00:31:24,105 --> 00:31:26,025
Sir, please tell me what can I do?

318
00:31:26,105 --> 00:31:27,145
I don't know.

319
00:31:28,265 --> 00:31:30,785
Get him out of there at any cost.

320
00:31:30,865 --> 00:31:32,185
Saxena sahib--

321
00:31:32,265 --> 00:31:33,905
Don't waste time, Arjun!

322
00:31:33,985 --> 00:31:38,745
And don't forget that Suresh
was working for your friend, Gujjar too.

323
00:31:39,265 --> 00:31:43,065
<i>And one more thing.</i>
<i>Choudhary is also in Al Dera now.</i>

324
00:32:53,865 --> 00:32:57,025
Thanks for taking my call
and picking me up.

325
00:32:58,185 --> 00:32:59,065
Rahul!

326
00:33:04,705 --> 00:33:05,905
Are you mad at me?

327
00:33:15,265 --> 00:33:19,065
Hey! Why would you think I'm mad at you?

328
00:33:26,025 --> 00:33:29,385
Choudhary sahib, I've picked her up.
We are coming straight to you.

329
00:33:41,825 --> 00:33:43,225
Hey! What are you talking about?

330
00:33:45,625 --> 00:33:46,905
Read the details at number two.

331
00:33:47,705 --> 00:33:50,465
<i>Aero details, Flight AEO-017.</i>

332
00:33:51,145 --> 00:33:53,065
<i>Cargo details, 40 coffins.</i> So?

333
00:33:53,145 --> 00:33:56,545
But it doesn't state that each coffin
comes with 50 kilos of yellow.

334
00:33:56,625 --> 00:33:57,705
How much?

335
00:33:57,785 --> 00:33:59,145
- Fifty kilos.
- Fifty kilos.

336
00:33:59,225 --> 00:34:00,305
Are you serious?

337
00:34:00,945 --> 00:34:03,425
We will head for the cargo terminal soon.

338
00:34:03,505 --> 00:34:04,345
Yes, sir.

339
00:34:14,865 --> 00:34:16,744
Get the car.
I've to go to the cargo terminal.

340
00:35:47,825 --> 00:35:49,505
Who's the clearing agent here?

341
00:35:50,145 --> 00:35:50,985
It's me, sir.

342
00:35:52,585 --> 00:35:53,825
Put this in the scanner.

343
00:35:53,905 --> 00:35:56,425
Sahib, their families
have been waiting since 10:30 am.

344
00:35:56,505 --> 00:35:59,345
If I tell them that we're
scanning their deceased relatives,

345
00:35:59,425 --> 00:36:01,545
- sahib, it will lead to chaos.
- Let it be.

346
00:36:01,625 --> 00:36:02,785
Take these away.

347
00:36:02,865 --> 00:36:04,625
- Come on, guys. Let's go.
- Come on.

348
00:36:04,705 --> 00:36:05,985
Get all the boxes loaded.

349
00:36:27,465 --> 00:36:28,465
I know who it is.

350
00:36:28,545 --> 00:36:30,185
Two tons of gold has to reach India.

351
00:36:30,265 --> 00:36:32,905
Coffins would be perfect
for such a huge consignment.

352
00:36:35,705 --> 00:36:37,305
It's time for our cargo.

353
00:36:38,665 --> 00:36:40,385
Our gold won't be sent in coffins,

354
00:36:40,465 --> 00:36:43,865
but in furniture,
as diplomatic cargo on the other flight.

355
00:38:13,785 --> 00:38:16,425
- Which cargo is this?
- Diplomatic cargo, sir.

356
00:38:16,505 --> 00:38:18,785
- From where?
- From the Kingdom of Burundi.

357
00:38:20,025 --> 00:38:23,145
- What's in there?
- It's the diplomat's personal furniture.

358
00:40:19,425 --> 00:40:20,265
Yes?

359
00:40:22,585 --> 00:40:26,185
Choudhary sahib, first of all,
thank you for sparing my life.

360
00:40:28,305 --> 00:40:30,585
But you'll never
be able to achieve the goal

361
00:40:31,905 --> 00:40:33,785
for which you spared my life.

362
00:40:35,745 --> 00:40:37,545
Arjun will never befriend you.

363
00:40:38,305 --> 00:40:39,785
That's bad news for you.

364
00:40:40,865 --> 00:40:42,665
And the bad news for you is that

365
00:40:42,745 --> 00:40:45,625
you don't even know the name of the person

366
00:40:46,305 --> 00:40:48,505
who was being tipped off
by Suresh <i>kaka</i> all this time.

367
00:40:49,865 --> 00:40:51,545
So long as that person is active,

368
00:40:52,825 --> 00:40:55,145
people like Suresh
will keep popping up in your syndicate.

369
00:40:58,305 --> 00:41:01,665
If you wish, I can get Suresh <i>kaka</i>
to disclose that man's identity.

370
00:41:07,105 --> 00:41:11,585
And what makes you think
that we are not capable of doing that?

371
00:41:14,345 --> 00:41:17,865
I'm sure, you must have tried
in the past few hours.

372
00:41:51,345 --> 00:41:53,225
- Good afternoon, sir.
- Good afternoon.

373
00:41:53,305 --> 00:41:55,425
Is somebody here
for this diplomatic cargo?

374
00:41:55,505 --> 00:41:57,145
Yes, sir. Their agents are outside.

375
00:41:57,745 --> 00:41:58,985
You can go. I'll check it.

376
00:42:48,385 --> 00:42:51,385
If your source gets compromised
12 hours before dispatch,

377
00:42:52,305 --> 00:42:54,305
would you still let the consignment go?

378
00:42:58,185 --> 00:42:59,305
Well, Arjun?

379
00:43:00,665 --> 00:43:05,185
If your source gets compromised
12 hours before dispatch,

380
00:43:06,025 --> 00:43:08,505
would you still let the consignment go?

381
00:43:09,865 --> 00:43:10,905
Forget 12,

382
00:43:11,505 --> 00:43:14,785
if I find out even three hours before,
I'll cancel the flight.

383
00:43:18,825 --> 00:43:20,745
There will be no gold in the coffins.

384
00:43:25,465 --> 00:43:26,305
Yes, Mitali.

385
00:43:26,385 --> 00:43:28,025
- Arjun.
<i>- Yes, tell me.</i>

386
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:29,825
No gold was found here. It's all clean.

387
00:43:41,505 --> 00:43:44,345
- When did this flight land?
- Just two hours ago.

388
00:43:44,985 --> 00:43:47,745
- And where is its cargo?
- In Warehouse number 2, sir.

389
00:43:54,385 --> 00:43:56,305
Sir, it's diplomatic cargo,

390
00:43:56,385 --> 00:43:58,425
and household furniture. Sir!

391
00:45:13,705 --> 00:45:18,185
{\an8}Suresh <i>kaka!</i> Tell me,
who did you pass the information to?

392
00:45:18,265 --> 00:45:19,745
<i>Kaka,</i> just a little while longer.

393
00:45:23,945 --> 00:45:26,905
Choudhary sahib has promised
that he will not kill you.

394
00:45:26,985 --> 00:45:28,345
Promise?

395
00:45:53,825 --> 00:45:56,185
Move. Go, go, go!

396
00:46:36,225 --> 00:46:37,545
Give me the name.

397
00:46:55,265 --> 00:46:56,385
Suresh, give me the name.

398
00:46:58,425 --> 00:46:59,345
Say it!

399
00:47:00,105 --> 00:47:00,945
Say it!

400
00:47:21,065 --> 00:47:22,465
I have checked it all.

401
00:47:31,625 --> 00:47:32,585
Take it up.

402
00:47:38,825 --> 00:47:39,785
I'll call you back.

403
00:47:40,385 --> 00:47:41,545
Take it inside.

404
00:47:44,185 --> 00:47:45,185
Arjun!

405
00:47:46,785 --> 00:47:47,705
What're you doing?

406
00:47:47,785 --> 00:47:48,785
I am checking, sir.

407
00:47:50,305 --> 00:47:51,665
This cargo is clear.

408
00:47:53,225 --> 00:47:55,865
If Customs has any suspicions,
we can check it.

409
00:47:57,225 --> 00:48:00,505
Arjun, this is diplomatic cargo.
We cannot open it.

410
00:48:02,385 --> 00:48:04,985
Sir, we have reasons to believe,
this cargo contains gold.

411
00:48:05,585 --> 00:48:06,905
And we need to inspect it.

412
00:48:10,225 --> 00:48:11,425
What's your problem?

413
00:48:12,745 --> 00:48:15,345
We cannot check diplomatic cargo.

414
00:48:15,425 --> 00:48:16,345
Don't you know that?

415
00:48:17,025 --> 00:48:19,585
It will be checked, Mr. Prakash Kumar.

416
00:48:22,505 --> 00:48:25,945
Excuse me? What did you say?

417
00:48:26,025 --> 00:48:27,505
It will be checked.

418
00:48:27,585 --> 00:48:28,505
Arjun!

419
00:48:29,825 --> 00:48:30,785
Stop it!

420
00:48:41,065 --> 00:48:42,065
Arjun!

421
00:48:56,305 --> 00:48:57,705
Suresh, give me the name.

422
00:49:07,865 --> 00:49:10,665
Freeze! Nobody moves! Don't move!

423
00:49:10,745 --> 00:49:12,345
Drop your weapons! Drop your weapons!

424
00:49:14,505 --> 00:49:15,705
On your knees!

425
00:49:23,225 --> 00:49:26,185
Do not move! Surrender!

426
00:49:26,865 --> 00:49:28,905
You cannot escape.

427
00:49:28,985 --> 00:49:31,665
You have been surrounded from all sides!

428
00:49:36,665 --> 00:49:38,625
There is no way to escape.

429
00:49:38,705 --> 00:49:40,185
You have been surrounded!

430
00:49:40,265 --> 00:49:42,345
I repeat, surrender!

431
00:49:48,305 --> 00:49:50,585
We'll be tracking you all the time. Okay?

432
00:49:51,345 --> 00:49:54,185
It's okay, Arjun. I'll be fine. Trust me.

433
00:49:56,305 --> 00:49:57,185
Really?

434
00:49:59,105 --> 00:50:00,465
Aren't you scared?

435
00:50:03,025 --> 00:50:03,945
No.

436
00:50:05,385 --> 00:50:06,905
I know you have my back.

437
00:50:18,105 --> 00:50:20,345
- Take care.
- I will.

438
00:50:21,825 --> 00:50:22,665
Yes, Arjun?

439
00:50:22,745 --> 00:50:23,825
Govind.

440
00:50:23,905 --> 00:50:25,425
Go in with full backup.

441
00:50:26,065 --> 00:50:29,065
The place where Priya is going,
entire Choudhary Syndicate will be there.

442
00:50:29,145 --> 00:50:30,905
Well armed. Okay?

443
00:50:30,985 --> 00:50:32,105
Don't worry.

444
00:50:32,185 --> 00:50:33,105
<i>We'll be prepared.</i>

445
00:50:39,105 --> 00:50:40,025
Priya!

446
00:51:40,265 --> 00:51:42,305
Go, go, go, go!

447
00:51:42,385 --> 00:51:45,065
Don't move.

448
00:51:45,145 --> 00:51:46,745
<i>Our external agencies…</i>

449
00:51:47,865 --> 00:51:49,745
<i>…shared the intelligence</i>
<i>they had gathered</i>

450
00:51:49,825 --> 00:51:52,065
<i>about Choudhary Syndicate</i>
<i>with foreign agencies.</i>

451
00:51:52,145 --> 00:51:55,505
<i>And as a result,</i>
<i>all of Choudhary's locations were raided.</i>

452
00:51:56,505 --> 00:51:58,385
{\an8}<i>And his business was shut down.</i>

453
00:51:58,465 --> 00:52:01,505
Don't move.

454
00:52:25,865 --> 00:52:27,585
You messed it all up.

455
00:52:29,105 --> 00:52:30,785
Listen, I can explain this. Okay?

456
00:52:32,585 --> 00:52:33,705
You guys are immature.

457
00:52:33,785 --> 00:52:35,225
What will you do, huh?

458
00:52:40,705 --> 00:52:41,705
Mitali!

459
00:57:33,425 --> 00:57:38,425
Subtitle translation by: Monika Saraf
